The Universal Light Capsule, v4.0: A Closed‑Loop Protocol for Interstellar Optical Communication

Author: ouadi Maakoul 

Abstract

We present the Universal Light Capsule (ULC), a mathematically rigorous, physically grounded protocol for interstellar communication with unknown intelligences. Building on algorithmic information theory, modern deep‑space optical standards, and algebraic topology, the ULC v4.0 introduces: (1) a computable artificiality threshold based on randomized time‑bounded Kolmogorov complexity (rKt), with a self‑delimiting Mersenne prime handshake that provably separates designed signals from natural stochastic processes; (2) a physical layer synchronized to the hydrogen 21 cm line, where the receiver recovers the slot clock by finding the greatest common divisor of pulse intervals; (3) a topological encoding layer using adjacency matrices of simplicial complexes, conveying the Euler characteristic and manifold connectivity without symbolic ambiguity; (4) a concatenated coding architecture (SCPPM + Reed–Solomon) with an interleaver seeded by the handshake itself, enabling self‑bootstrapping; and (5) a “Physics Lingo” that encodes tensor equations as relational bitmaps, providing a functional manual for general relativity. 

