The search for extraterrestrial intelligence (SETI) has historically relied on radio and optical signals encoded using human‑centric conventions (decimal numerals, ASCII, terrestrial imagery). Such approaches presuppose shared biological or cultural priors that cannot be guaranteed across cosmic distances. The Universal Light Capsule (ULC) addresses this epistemic gap by constructing a transmission protocol grounded in mathematical necessity and physical universality.

