2. Mathematical Foundations & Formal Verification

2.1 Binary Primacy and the Principle of Sufficient Reason

The ULC adopts binary modulation as its foundational substrate, justified by the Principle of Sufficient Reason: the minimal distinguishable states are existence (1) and absence (0). To ensure recognition as artificial, the transmission employs Pulse‑Position Modulation (PPM) with inter‑pulse intervals drawn from a deterministic, non‑stochastic sequence.

2.2 Formalizing the “Artificiality” Detection Metric: rKt and the Self‑Delimiting Handshake

We replace generic entropy thresholds with a computable metric from algorithmic information theory: randomized time‑bounded Kolmogorov complexity (rKt). For a string  w , define:

\text{rKt}(w) = \min \{ |p| + \lceil \log_2 t \rceil : U(p) \text{ outputs } w \text{ in } t \text{ steps with probability } > 2/3 \}

where  U  is a universal Turing machine equipped with random bits. This metric is computable in practice via time‑limited search.

Artificiality Threshold: Let  |w|  be the length of the received handshake sequence. Choose a constant  K  (e.g.,  K = 10 ) such that if:

\text{rKt}(w) \leq |w| - K

then  w  is formally classified as an intentional artifact.

Optimal Handshake Proof (Self‑Delimiting Property): The ULC transmits the first  n  Mersenne primes  M_n = 2^{p_n} - 1 , where  p_n  is the  n -th prime. This sequence is self‑delimiting: because each prime is strictly larger than the previous one, the receiver can uniquely parse the concatenated binary stream without requiring explicit separators. The raw length  |w|  grows as  O(n^2 \log n) . However, the shortest program that generates the sequence (sieve of Eratosthenes plus the Mersenne formula) has length  O(\log n + \text{constant}) , and the computation time  t  (Lucas–Lehmer primality test) is polynomial in  n , so  \log_2 t  is negligible. The artificiality gap:

\Delta = |w| - \text{rKt}(w) \to \infty \quad \text{as } n \to \infty

No known natural stochastic process (pulsar, quantum fluctuation, accretion disk turbulence) can produce a gap  \Delta > K  for large  n , because natural processes are either truly random (high rKt) or have simple periodicities (low raw length). Hence, a sufficiently large  \Delta  constitutes a mathematical proof of intelligence.

2.3 Base‑Independent Geometric Constants via Convergent Series

Constants are transmitted as limits of convergent series, independent of numeral system.

Circular Constant  \pi : Encoded via the Bailey–Borwein–Plouffe (BBP) formula:

